modules.description: This module formats log messages using `strf`, maps log levels to command line arguments with `level_arg`, and selects the last element of a list with `last_of_list`. It defines a command line interface for logging options using `level`, integrating with `cmdliner` to handle environment variables, documentation sections, and debug flags. It is used to configure logging verbosity and behavior through command line arguments in applications.

Sets up terminal-based logging with customizable output formatting and log levels. It configures a logs reporter for a given console interface, allowing optional style rendering and log level filtering. This module is used to direct application logs to the terminal with visual styling and controlled verbosity, such as during command-line tool execution.

This module provides terminal logging configuration and command-line log-level handling. It supports styled log output with level filtering and integrates with `cmdliner` for CLI log options. Used to set up terminal logging and parse logging settings from command line arguments.
